@node "hist" "History"
@toc "alko"

            v1.0 - First public release. Uses packing routines v0.4.
            Although the version number is 0.4 @{b}the routines are complete
            and fully functioning.@{ub}
@endnode

@node "ass" "Assebler users"
@toc "alko"

            We have included the assembly-sources of zero-packer
            and -unpacker here. They lie in the Asm-directory.

            zero packer   v0.4.@{"asm" link "Asm/zer°!packer!v0.4.S/Main" 0}
            zero unpacker v0.4.@{"asm" link "Asm/zer°!unpacker!v0.4.S/Main" 0}

            And here are the safer version, which have the complete
            error detection (which makes them a little slower).

            zero packer   v0.4.@{"asm" link "Asm/zer°!packer!v0.4!safe.S/Main" 0}
            zero unpacker v0.4.@{"asm" link "Asm/zer°!unpacker!v0.4!safe.S/Main" 0}

            @{b}If you use these sources in your own production, then
            you must credits us - RRR's Utility Division.@{ub}
@endnode

@node "algo" "Algorhytm"
@toc alko

            Here is zpk's packet-format:

            .L Packet's lenght (zpk)
            .L Original lenght (bin)
            .B Header (Marks the packed points)
            .. Packed data

            Zpk goes through the data and when a zero has been found
            it marks the spot and tries to look some more.
            After finding a zero, zpk counts the other zeroes and inserts
            the header and the number of zeroes into the packet.

            Like this:

            .B Header
            .L Number of zeroes

            Piece of cake.
@endnode

